# Keep the Docker build context small and avoid sending host-only artifacts.
#
# The frontend image installs its own dependencies (npm ci) and runs its own
# `npm run build` inside the container, so none of these local directories are
# needed. Excluding node_modules also sidesteps "error from sender ...
# permission denied" failures when the local Vite cache (node_modules/.vite)
# was written by a different host user and isn't world-readable.

node_modules
dist
.vite

# Local env files must never leak into the image. The frontend gets its
# config (VITE_API_URL etc.) via Docker build args, not bundled .env files.
.env
.env.*

# Misc local artifacts
coverage
storybook-static
*.log
.DS_Store
